All updates I'll be talking about were completed by 3 to 4 people.

51
00:02:37,236 --> 00:02:39,117
So, Rocket Racing.

52
00:02:39,838 --> 00:02:41,498
Hands up if you've played this game.

53
00:02:43,107 --> 00:02:46,130
See how there's like no hands up? This game was a disaster.

54
00:02:46,510 --> 00:02:49,974
This was a game we made a couple of years ago for PSP minis.

55
00:02:50,794 --> 00:02:55,559
And this game was a hardcore, abstract racing game that we made.

56
00:02:56,179 --> 00:03:00,063
We spent eight months on this game. We really poured a lot into it and it

57
00:03:00,563 --> 00:03:01,965
absolutely bombed.

58
00:03:02,625 --> 00:03:07,109
It was, you know, it got an okay-ish critical reception but just, you know,

59
00:03:07,370 --> 00:03:08,571
there was no market for it.

60
00:03:10,577 --> 00:03:12,580
So it's because of this game that we had this new goal.

61
00:03:13,221 --> 00:03:14,763
And this new goal was to ship lean,

62
00:03:15,484 --> 00:03:18,048
you know, ship multiple games really lean, really quickly.

63
00:03:18,529 --> 00:03:20,492
And if it works, we'll update it often.

64
00:03:20,852 --> 00:03:23,476
And this way, we'll be lowering our risk of development.

65
00:03:24,057 --> 00:03:24,918
I'm just going to move this here.

66
00:03:26,948 --> 00:03:29,989
So that's where Fruit Ninja comes in.

67
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:33,690
Fruit Ninja is a direct result of Rocket Racing.

68
00:03:33,790 --> 00:03:37,391
It was me trying to make the opposite game to Rocket Racing.

69
00:03:38,332 --> 00:03:42,053
What we have here is like 80% of the design document

70
00:03:42,093 --> 00:03:43,373
that exists for Fruit Ninja.

71
00:03:44,053 --> 00:03:46,294
This is all there has been and all there probably ever

72
00:03:46,334 --> 00:03:47,394
will be for Fruit Ninja.

73
00:03:48,755 --> 00:03:49,535
You know, pretty simple.

74
00:03:49,615 --> 00:03:51,075
Slice fruit, don't slice bombs.

75
00:03:51,696 --> 00:03:54,016
And when we shipped, we shipped really lean.

76
00:03:55,457 --> 00:03:59,265
almost crazy like you look at Fruit Ninja and if you're familiar with the game at the moment you

77
00:03:59,305 --> 00:04:04,295
know it has you know like four modes and unlockables and achievements and leaderboards

78
00:04:04,335 --> 00:04:06,860
and social features and all kinds of crazy stuff.

79
00:04:07,732 --> 00:04:10,095
Version 1.0 had nothing.

80
00:04:10,695 --> 00:04:11,936
It was so, so lean.

81
00:04:11,956 --> 00:04:12,777
There were no modes.

82
00:04:12,817 --> 00:04:14,799
There's only what now we know is classic mode.

83
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,341
There were no combos.

84
00:04:16,401 --> 00:04:17,341
There were no unlocks.

85
00:04:17,782 --> 00:04:19,824
There were very few devices we had to worry about.

86
00:04:19,844 --> 00:04:22,426
There was no such thing as Game Center or Retina

87
00:04:22,446 --> 00:04:23,407
or any of that stuff.

88
00:04:23,467 --> 00:04:24,829
And because of all these factors,

89
00:04:24,869 --> 00:04:27,091
we actually shipped the game in six weeks

90
00:04:27,972 --> 00:04:31,195
from start to finish just with three guys,

91
00:04:31,275 --> 00:04:32,996
plus a sound guy for a week as well.

92
00:04:33,882 --> 00:04:36,103
I was looking for a screenshot of Old Fruit Ninja.

93
00:04:36,143 --> 00:04:37,163
I couldn't even find that.

94
00:04:37,283 --> 00:04:39,964
This screenshot has got multi-touch in it.

95
00:04:40,764 --> 00:04:41,504
1.0 didn't even have that.

96
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:44,325
I just couldn't find an older screenshot than this one.

97
00:04:46,626 --> 00:04:48,226
So when we launched, everything went really well.

98
00:04:48,266 --> 00:04:49,747
We got a really good critical reception.

99
00:04:50,447 --> 00:04:52,988
We got good reviews all over the place, which was very cool.

100
00:04:54,188 --> 00:04:56,469
I couldn't find any cool screenshots of us

101
00:04:56,689 --> 00:04:58,510
at our early stages of success, so you

102
00:04:58,530 --> 00:05:01,110
have to make do with my artist's interpretation right here.

103
00:05:02,421 --> 00:05:03,764
Yeah, I'm not an artist, I'm a designer.

104
00:05:05,828 --> 00:05:09,917
And so the game is out, we have 1.0, and time for some updates.

105
00:05:10,137 --> 00:05:12,281
So this is really, you know, what the talk is about.

106
00:05:14,763 --> 00:05:20,244
Update 1.01. So this is our very first update and our goal was pretty simple. We wanted to roll an update

107
00:05:20,404 --> 00:05:24,185
really soon after launch and show everyone that we were committed to this game, we were going to be

108
00:05:24,225 --> 00:05:29,706
supporting this game and although this game is simple, there's more to come. We started working

109
00:05:29,766 --> 00:05:34,287
on this before the game was even out while we were waiting for it to pass like Apple certification

110
00:05:34,307 --> 00:05:37,128
and all of that stuff. So our current player base was zero.

111
00:05:39,103 --> 00:05:42,964
And it's pretty simple, you know, we were going to add two new fruit, the mango and the pear,

112
00:05:43,144 --> 00:05:46,424
which, you know, we add new fruit now, no one really cares because we've got such a large

113
00:05:46,724 --> 00:05:49,585
roster, but back then we didn't have that many, so that was kind of a big deal.

114
00:05:50,005 --> 00:05:53,866
We wanted to do multi-touch support, so that you could have multiple blades,

115
00:05:53,906 --> 00:05:57,206
which seemed like it'd be a cool thing. And we wanted to just, we knew that the performance

116
00:05:57,306 --> 00:06:01,047
wasn't that great, especially on the older devices. We knew there was a lot we could

117
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:03,728
do to make that better, so we were really focusing on that.

118
00:06:05,568 --> 00:06:06,968
So I have a bit of a story here for you.

119
00:06:09,550 --> 00:06:13,471
Fruit Ninja came out and it was doing pretty good, you know, it was moving up the charts

120
00:06:13,531 --> 00:06:15,352
and in Australia it was doing really well.

121
00:06:15,652 --> 00:06:19,814
So it's a Friday night and Fruit Ninja overtook Doodle Jump in the charts.

122
00:06:19,914 --> 00:06:23,976
It was still way down in the American charts, you know, position 120 or something,

123
00:06:24,196 --> 00:06:26,597
but it was doing really good in Australia and we were stoked.

124
00:06:26,637 --> 00:06:29,498
So we were having our traditional Friday afternoon beers

125
00:06:29,979 --> 00:06:34,161
and obviously because things were going well we were having a few extra beers to celebrate

126
00:06:34,281 --> 00:06:37,862
and, you know, really getting into the spirit of things, so to say.

127
00:06:38,342 --> 00:06:39,403
And it got to about...

128
00:06:40,465 --> 00:06:44,772
11 o'clock or so and we got an email that came in, don't ask us why we were checking

129
00:06:44,852 --> 00:06:48,599
emails while we were drinking, and it was an email from Apple telling us that they wanted

130
00:06:48,619 --> 00:06:51,924
to feature us and that they needed the assets immediately.

131
00:06:53,951 --> 00:06:57,552
So being in Australia, it was our Friday afternoon.

132
00:06:57,572 --> 00:07:00,292
They probably sent it on their Thursday afternoon or Friday

133
00:07:00,332 --> 00:07:01,752
morning, thinking that we would have time.

134
00:07:01,772 --> 00:07:03,233
But because it was going to be our weekend

135
00:07:03,293 --> 00:07:04,693
and no one was going to be there, we were like, right,

136
00:07:04,713 --> 00:07:06,193
we're going to do these assets right away.

137
00:07:06,553 --> 00:07:10,034
We entered full panic mode and kind of semi-drunkenly

138
00:07:10,074 --> 00:07:15,215
got all these assets together, which was really cool.

139
00:07:15,975 --> 00:07:17,756
You wouldn't want to do that again in hindsight.

140
00:07:17,816 --> 00:07:20,696
But we're usually a lot more prepared than that now.

141
00:07:20,736 --> 00:07:21,976
We learn our lesson from that one.

142
00:07:22,858 --> 00:07:23,979
So then two things happen.

143
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:28,263
The very first update launches at the exact same time

144
00:07:28,303 --> 00:07:29,565
that we get featured by Apple.

145
00:07:30,606 --> 00:07:31,326
And we're stoked.

146
00:07:31,647 --> 00:07:33,449
Featured by Apple, that's a huge deal.

147
00:07:33,529 --> 00:07:35,210
It's going to help our sales dramatically.

148
00:07:35,230 --> 00:07:36,952
We're going to get all this extra exposure, all

149
00:07:36,992 --> 00:07:38,013
this extra attention.

150
00:07:38,514 --> 00:07:38,794
Awesome.

151
00:07:38,834 --> 00:07:40,336
And it's right when the update lands.

152
00:07:40,636 --> 00:07:41,697
That's amazing, right?

153
00:07:43,925 --> 00:07:47,767
Boom. This update was a disaster.

154
00:07:48,788 --> 00:07:51,249
Unfortunately, when we were working on

155
00:07:51,449 --> 00:07:54,371
the updates and the

156
00:07:55,131 --> 00:07:59,573
performance fixes, we had obviously screwed something up pretty dramatically

157
00:07:59,653 --> 00:08:00,474
and for some reason

158
00:08:00,614 --> 00:08:03,395
about 15 percent of players could no longer play the game.

159
00:08:03,916 --> 00:08:07,537
And this was the worst time, you know, we just sort of got this momentum going, we just

160
00:08:07,577 --> 00:08:09,398
got featured and then this update came.

161
00:08:10,116 --> 00:08:15,582
and all of a sudden the one star reviews are flying in and we're in full panic mode.

162
00:08:16,182 --> 00:08:17,403
So we need to do a new update.

163
00:08:21,206 --> 00:08:23,548
1.01.1. Pretty simple goal.

164
00:08:23,608 --> 00:08:25,890
And we were fortunate enough, we got it fixed really quickly.

165
00:08:25,910 --> 00:08:29,973
And it was actually really interesting, like, you know,

166
00:08:30,353 --> 00:08:33,556
obviously when this happened and, you know, it's locking people out of the game,

167
00:08:33,576 --> 00:08:35,838
we're thinking it's this massive disaster and,

168
00:08:36,318 --> 00:08:38,700
you know, oh shit, the game is doomed forever.

169
00:08:39,681 --> 00:08:43,324
But there was this, it was really interesting, we got it fixed, we

170
00:08:43,684 --> 00:08:46,807
ended up kind of nicknaming these builds where we fixed the problem.

171
00:08:47,387 --> 00:08:48,648
uh, firefighter builds.

172
00:08:49,408 --> 00:08:51,069
Um, and we got this silver lining

173
00:08:51,109 --> 00:08:53,070
where people really seemed to respond to the fact

174
00:08:53,130 --> 00:08:54,971
that we took notice that we'd done

175
00:08:55,031 --> 00:08:57,072
something wrong and that the game had sort of become

176
00:08:57,152 --> 00:08:59,213
unstable, and we fixed

177
00:08:59,273 --> 00:09:01,334
it really quickly. You know, we were communicating,

178
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:03,195
we were on forums, we were replying

179
00:09:03,215 --> 00:09:04,776
to emails saying we're on it, and then

180
00:09:05,216 --> 00:09:07,057
we did fix it. Certainly

181
00:09:07,097 --> 00:09:09,178
we lost people because, you know, they

182
00:09:09,258 --> 00:09:11,019
tried to play the game and it was no good and they felt

183
00:09:11,059 --> 00:09:13,180
like they'd been jipped out of their dollar, but, you know,

184
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:14,140
we also, uh...

185
00:09:15,097 --> 00:09:19,080
won some fans because you know they were watching us, they could see that we cared and that we were

186
00:09:19,180 --> 00:09:20,982
you know doing our best to keep things going.

187
00:09:22,323 --> 00:09:25,686
So we learn a few lessons pretty quickly on this one. You know updates can be

188
00:09:25,746 --> 00:09:26,847
crippling, certainly

189
00:09:27,687 --> 00:09:31,210
updates can enhance your game but at the same way it can take away from it.

190
00:09:32,011 --> 00:09:35,734
I'm sure there's some other iOS developers that could attest to that one.

191
00:09:35,754 --> 00:09:39,798
I think it was Minigore might have had a really bad one once that wiped progress and...

192
00:09:40,532 --> 00:09:43,732
you know, it's certainly something to be careful of. And so, you know, we realized

193
00:09:43,752 --> 00:09:47,173
that QA effort needed to be increased dramatically for these updates. We really

194
00:09:47,213 --> 00:09:50,074
hadn't given the update the QA time it deserved.

195
00:09:50,314 --> 00:09:54,195
We also needed to, you know, assess our risk associated with each update.

196
00:09:54,255 --> 00:09:56,976
Adding new fruit? Easy. That's cheap. That's probably pretty low risk.

197
00:09:57,016 --> 00:10:00,237
But being in there, mucking around with the render code, trying to make it run faster?

198
00:10:01,453 --> 00:10:05,221
getting in dangerous waters. We also realized that players are keeping score on us,

199
00:10:05,822 --> 00:10:08,688
which was interesting. We really didn't think people would be paying

200
00:10:08,788 --> 00:10:11,454
that much attention to Halfbrick, but it turns out they are.

201
00:10:13,258 --> 00:10:15,920
So at this point we get to update 1.2.

202
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:18,481
Our player base has grown dramatically now,

203
00:10:19,641 --> 00:10:20,982
145,000 players, which at the time

204
00:10:21,042 --> 00:10:22,442
seemed like the entire world.

205
00:10:22,482 --> 00:10:23,103
We were stoked.

206
00:10:23,923 --> 00:10:25,884
And our goal was to release something big that

207
00:10:25,924 --> 00:10:29,125
would warrant a second trailer and another round of media.

208
00:10:29,165 --> 00:10:31,066
And we really wanted to capitalize

209
00:10:31,126 --> 00:10:32,887
on this initial momentum we had going.

210
00:10:34,067 --> 00:10:36,789
So we weren't really sure which way to go with this.

211
00:10:37,989 --> 00:10:40,310
So it's tricky, because a game like

212
00:10:42,745 --> 00:10:45,768
Angry Birds, Cut the Rope, a lot of those level-based games,

213
00:10:46,488 --> 00:10:48,469
they have such a good way of updating the game.

214
00:10:48,509 --> 00:10:51,031
Like, you like our game, you like playing levels, boom!

215
00:10:51,632 --> 00:10:54,354
25 more levels. It's so simple, it's easy for them to add.

216
00:10:54,494 --> 00:10:57,036
The value proposition for the players is obvious.

217
00:10:57,056 --> 00:10:59,878
Like, there is now more of what you like to play,

218
00:10:59,938 --> 00:11:01,399
and it's just so easy to communicate.

219
00:11:01,419 --> 00:11:03,500
We didn't have anything like that for Fruit Ninja.

220
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:05,462
We really weren't sure on which way to go with it.

221
00:11:06,792 --> 00:11:09,855
So our producer, Jason Harwood, had this idea.

222
00:11:10,115 --> 00:11:14,019
And he went through every single iTunes review

223
00:11:14,079 --> 00:11:16,000
we had gotten so far, and he collated it

224
00:11:16,060 --> 00:11:17,602
into this massive Excel sheet.

225
00:11:17,882 --> 00:11:23,187
And then he grouped up common suggestions that people had

226
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:24,208
and common problems.

227
00:11:24,228 --> 00:11:27,551
So we had a section for bugs, a section for suggestions,

228
00:11:27,591 --> 00:11:28,591
and all of that kind of stuff.

229
00:11:29,572 --> 00:11:31,194
And this is what we ended up with.

230
00:11:32,436 --> 00:11:35,700
So the very top one there is, you know, multi-slice and then we have

231
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:39,704
needs more game modes, needs some kind of endless mode,

232
00:11:39,764 --> 00:11:43,928
that there's more fruit, so on. And it was all organized by the number of mentions it had.

233
00:11:45,310 --> 00:11:46,671
So number one, multi-slice.

234
00:11:48,447 --> 00:11:52,589
This still gets requested all the time,

235
00:11:52,889 --> 00:11:55,351
and every time I am against multi-slice.

236
00:11:55,411 --> 00:11:58,192
The thing is, right now in Fruit Ninja,

237
00:11:58,312 --> 00:12:00,073
the fruit is either sliced or it's not sliced.

238
00:12:00,133 --> 00:12:00,874
It's binary.

239
00:12:01,374 --> 00:12:03,735
The call to action for the player is so obvious.

240
00:12:03,795 --> 00:12:05,756
If the fruit isn't sliced, I need to slice it.

241
00:12:05,816 --> 00:12:08,057
As soon as you introduce this idea of multi-slice,

242
00:12:08,097 --> 00:12:09,498
things start to get trickier.

243
00:12:09,978 --> 00:12:11,979
There's now, you know, it's been sliced,

244
00:12:12,019 --> 00:12:13,800
but I could get more points if I don't.

245
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:15,201
There's an opportunity cost there.

246
00:12:15,721 --> 00:12:19,905
And additionally, as the fruit gets quartered and maybe eighth or sixteenth,

247
00:12:20,785 --> 00:12:25,689
it's actually getting smaller on the screen and it really stops becoming the optimal size for interacting with.

248
00:12:26,110 --> 00:12:30,073
So, multi-slice is something that I've been very much against for a long time.

249
00:12:32,475 --> 00:12:36,358
So, the second thing that, you know, second and third thing was, hey, more modes would be cool.

250
00:12:36,958 --> 00:12:39,380
And how about an infinite no-bomb mode?

251
00:12:40,307 --> 00:12:42,568
People really hated the bombs in classic mode.

252
00:12:42,628 --> 00:12:44,388
So we were like, OK, I get it.

253
00:12:44,428 --> 00:12:45,289
Bombs are kind of tricky.

254
00:12:45,349 --> 00:12:47,429
Let's try making this infinite no bomb mode.

255
00:12:48,170 --> 00:12:49,110
And it was interesting.

256
00:12:49,150 --> 00:12:50,130
We started working on it.

257
00:12:51,130 --> 00:12:52,651
We got it working really, really quickly.

258
00:12:52,851 --> 00:12:55,172
And for the first five minutes, it was really cool.

259
00:12:55,432 --> 00:12:58,533
And then slicing fruit all of a sudden lost its meaning.

260
00:12:59,745 --> 00:13:03,351
you it was really weird you kind of played in your life cool no bombs then

261
00:13:03,371 --> 00:13:06,235
there was no pressure and there was no kind of constraints

262
00:13:06,636 --> 00:13:10,141
and he sort of burnt out on slicing fruit which is bad news for a game that

263
00:13:10,181 --> 00:13:11,723
is only about slicing fruit

264
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:16,222
We tried some other things to really spice it up as well.

265
00:13:16,282 --> 00:13:18,803
We made this thing called critical waves,

266
00:13:18,883 --> 00:13:20,824
where all the fruit would come up and they would, you know,

267
00:13:21,004 --> 00:13:22,184
definitely be a critical.

268
00:13:22,965 --> 00:13:26,467
And the blade would turn blue and it would have sparkles on the back

269
00:13:26,507 --> 00:13:28,127
and that's how you knew that it was going to be a critical.

270
00:13:28,167 --> 00:13:30,669
And even that still didn't feel quite right.

271
00:13:30,729 --> 00:13:33,610
Just the points were meaningless and, you know,

272
00:13:33,850 --> 00:13:35,091
it really just wasn't clicking.

273
00:13:36,332 --> 00:13:38,973
Fortunately, we were able to use that blade stuff a little bit later on.

274
00:13:40,740 --> 00:13:45,143
So while we were working on this, we started mucking around with the idea of putting combos in.

275
00:13:45,163 --> 00:13:48,005
That was another common thread that had been in our iTunes reviews.

276
00:13:48,645 --> 00:13:52,488
I love this GIF just showing what the combos look like in slow-mo.

277
00:13:52,508 --> 00:13:53,768
I always think it looks really neat.

278
00:13:55,670 --> 00:13:59,872
And we put that in and we got a benefit from that straight away.

279
00:13:59,892 --> 00:14:01,794
It worked in classic mode.

280
00:14:02,274 --> 00:14:04,896
You could just slice the fruit or you could try and take bigger risks.

281
00:14:06,218 --> 00:14:08,139
One of the big things that we did was like rather than

282
00:14:08,159 --> 00:14:12,840
the score going up exponentially, so a four fruit combo being worth five points

283
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:15,461
and a five fruit combo being worth ten points or whatever,

284
00:14:15,941 --> 00:14:18,362
we really wanted it to be as simple as possible and

285
00:14:18,882 --> 00:14:22,683
make it so that people would understand what score they got and why immediately.

286
00:14:22,803 --> 00:14:27,164
So we kind of made some sacrifices to the gameplay

287
00:14:27,825 --> 00:14:32,246
in order to increase how clearly the game was communicating with the player.

288
00:14:35,327 --> 00:14:37,288
And then we added a time limit to Zen mode.

289
00:14:37,989 --> 00:14:40,511
And all of a sudden, it all kind of made sense.

290
00:14:40,631 --> 00:14:41,311
It was so weird.

291
00:14:41,331 --> 00:14:42,852
We added the 90-second time limit.

292
00:14:43,633 --> 00:14:44,913
And it was just this kind of like, well,

293
00:14:44,993 --> 00:14:46,674
it's annoying because it goes on forever

294
00:14:46,714 --> 00:14:48,055
and you have to hit the pause button.

295
00:14:48,456 --> 00:14:49,716
And then that's how you get out of the game.

296
00:14:49,736 --> 00:14:51,678
So maybe we'll just add a time limit, and that was it.

297
00:14:51,938 --> 00:14:52,998
We added this time limit.

298
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:54,219
Next thing you know, you look around,

299
00:14:54,259 --> 00:14:56,461
and all the guys are trying to beat each other's high scores.

300
00:14:57,041 --> 00:15:00,622
And this weird thing happened where Zen mode was now like both the most relaxing mode,

301
00:15:00,702 --> 00:15:03,723
or that's what it was intended to be, was this relaxing mode

302
00:15:04,083 --> 00:15:06,184
where you didn't have as much stress and pressure,

303
00:15:06,544 --> 00:15:10,945
to this extremely hardcore, competitive, everyone trying to beat each other's high scores,

304
00:15:12,466 --> 00:15:13,746
which was absolutely fantastic.

305
00:15:13,846 --> 00:15:16,407
And all of a sudden it felt Fruit Ninja again.

306
00:15:16,467 --> 00:15:17,747
It felt like it had a place.

307
00:15:18,248 --> 00:15:22,929
And a lot of the times it was just this kind of intuitive sense that it belonged in the game.

308
00:15:24,008 --> 00:15:27,452
We went through and we tuned the waves in Zen mode to make them

309
00:15:28,232 --> 00:15:31,335
play off that as well and they're all combo-able in different ways.

310
00:15:33,177 --> 00:15:36,780
The other thing we added was the coming soon fruit. We wanted people to know, yes, this is a

311
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:40,083
big update, but we're not done yet. We're not even close to done yet.

312
00:15:40,383 --> 00:15:43,546
We wanted everyone to know that we are still working on more stuff.

313
00:15:46,317 --> 00:15:48,340
So when we released, everything seemed to go pretty good.

314
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:50,644
We got quite a bit of coverage around the place, which was neat.

315
00:15:50,664 --> 00:15:53,948
You know, everything kind of worked how we expected.

316
00:15:54,009 --> 00:15:58,375
We said we wanted to warrant doing a second trailer and a big media blitz,

317
00:15:58,415 --> 00:15:59,376
and that definitely happened.

318
00:15:59,657 --> 00:16:01,560
Got really widespread coverage, which was great.

319
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:03,772
And then this is the graph for what happened.

320
00:16:03,812 --> 00:16:07,095
So the orange line is updates, the blue line is sales.

321
00:16:07,115 --> 00:16:09,538
They're not necessarily on the same scale,

322
00:16:09,558 --> 00:16:10,579
they're just kind of compressed

323
00:16:10,599 --> 00:16:11,780
so you can see what's going on.

324
00:16:12,100 --> 00:16:14,502
Otherwise, the blue line is really flat and at the bottom

325
00:16:14,542 --> 00:16:16,705
because the update volume is always so high.

326
00:16:17,665 --> 00:16:20,568
And you can see, you know, we were on this downward decline

327
00:16:20,588 --> 00:16:23,371
and we did this update and it helped.

328
00:16:24,255 --> 00:16:25,156
But not a great deal.

329
00:16:25,456 --> 00:16:27,097
You know, we spent a long time on Zenmode.

330
00:16:27,137 --> 00:16:28,377
Well, relatively long time.

331
00:16:28,417 --> 00:16:29,838
We spent three or four weeks on it,

332
00:16:29,858 --> 00:16:31,859
which is almost as long as it took to make the game.

333
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:34,600
And, you know, we got this bit of a bump

334
00:16:34,641 --> 00:16:35,841
and it stabilized us,

335
00:16:35,881 --> 00:16:38,843
but it certainly wasn't this big boom like we were expecting.

336
00:16:41,284 --> 00:16:42,905
So, again, lessons learned.

337
00:16:44,198 --> 00:16:47,159
We need to listen to the fans but read between the lines.

338
00:16:47,219 --> 00:16:49,680
And I mean, this isn't even something that's specific to,

339
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:52,201
you know, iTunes reviews and community feedback.

340
00:16:52,241 --> 00:16:54,101
This is just playtesting in general, right?

341
00:16:54,121 --> 00:16:57,942
You know, one of the ones I always remember is

342
00:16:58,082 --> 00:17:00,063
back when I was working on an old licensed game,

343
00:17:00,403 --> 00:17:03,344
we had some kids come in and we'd designed this puzzle game.

344
00:17:03,944 --> 00:17:05,985
And these kids were coming in and they were playing the game

345
00:17:06,085 --> 00:17:07,405
over and over and over and, you know,

346
00:17:07,445 --> 00:17:08,865
just kind of playing through the first part.

347
00:17:08,945 --> 00:17:11,486
And the kid got about 20 minutes in and he's going,

348
00:17:11,506 --> 00:17:12,566
you know what this game needs.

349
00:17:13,287 --> 00:17:14,527
I said to him, what does this game need?

350
00:17:14,547 --> 00:17:16,028
He goes, this game needs a tank.

351
00:17:16,868 --> 00:17:17,948
I want to run over things.

352
00:17:17,988 --> 00:17:19,189
I want to blow up the walls.

353
00:17:19,309 --> 00:17:20,709
And that's what I really want to do.

354
00:17:21,349 --> 00:17:23,910
And so the interesting thing about that

355
00:17:23,950 --> 00:17:26,751
was obviously we're not going to add a tank to this puzzle game.

356
00:17:27,091 --> 00:17:29,712
But what it really said to us was, OK, this game

357
00:17:29,752 --> 00:17:30,692
needs variety.

358
00:17:30,772 --> 00:17:32,773
It needs a greater sense of empowerment.

359
00:17:33,213 --> 00:17:37,274
And the same thing can be said for iTunes reviews,

360
00:17:37,715 --> 00:17:39,755
community feedback, and community engagement.

361
00:17:40,001 --> 00:17:43,283
We really need to read between the lines and be smart about what we do.

362
00:17:44,944 --> 00:17:48,766
They know what the problem is, they don't specifically know what the solution is always,

363
00:17:48,846 --> 00:17:50,887
although there are often some really great ideas.

364
00:17:52,088 --> 00:17:55,410
And the other thing was just that updates can help keep the momentum, but they're a

365
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:55,890
lot of work.

366
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:59,932
I mean, I'm sure a lot of people who've done iOS updates know that they take a while to

367
00:17:59,972 --> 00:18:00,352
get right.

368
00:18:02,354 --> 00:18:02,854
So update 1.2.1.

369
00:18:04,847 --> 00:18:08,230
current player base has grown to 350,000, so that's pretty cool.

370
00:18:08,310 --> 00:18:10,952
And we had this idea for this update.

371
00:18:11,232 --> 00:18:14,655
We kind of had taken inspiration from the very first update

372
00:18:14,675 --> 00:18:15,736
where we botched things up.

373
00:18:16,416 --> 00:18:18,638
We said, OK, we're introducing a new mode.

374
00:18:19,492 --> 00:18:20,572
that's a pretty big change.

375
00:18:20,972 --> 00:18:22,552
That's probably a pretty big risk.

376
00:18:22,953 --> 00:18:24,893
So let's do this update, and we're gonna call it,

377
00:18:25,373 --> 00:18:27,594
the way that we kind of internally phrase this update

378
00:18:27,634 --> 00:18:28,734
is a chaser update.

379
00:18:29,374 --> 00:18:31,115
So the idea is this, there's gonna be an update

380
00:18:31,135 --> 00:18:33,356
that drops again, really quickly

381
00:18:33,496 --> 00:18:34,996
after the major release update,

382
00:18:35,916 --> 00:18:39,077
and it's gonna have a couple of new interesting things,

383
00:18:39,337 --> 00:18:41,298
nothing major, not like another mode or anything,

384
00:18:41,338 --> 00:18:43,619
just some nice little extra bits and pieces,

385
00:18:44,219 --> 00:18:46,880
and we're also gonna roll all of the bug fixes

386
00:18:46,940 --> 00:18:49,280
and all the problems that come up into this update.

387
00:18:50,184 --> 00:18:54,647
The other thing we really wanted to do was, you know, spark some community engargement.

388
00:18:55,548 --> 00:18:59,171
Hmm. Okay. There's no spellcheck in Photoshop. I apologize.

389
00:19:00,632 --> 00:19:04,675
So what we did is we got some minor stuff ready beforehand.

390
00:19:04,855 --> 00:19:09,038
We added some coconuts and, you know, fixed a couple of bugs that we already knew of.

391
00:19:09,258 --> 00:19:13,341
And we had this stuff ready to go before Zenmode even dropped.

392
00:19:14,554 --> 00:19:17,057
The other things we added were rate us.

393
00:19:17,318 --> 00:19:20,701
So, really simple thing, comes up every now and then,

394
00:19:20,721 --> 00:19:22,003
you know, hey, how about you rate us?

395
00:19:23,044 --> 00:19:24,526
We were a bit smarter about it

396
00:19:25,307 --> 00:19:26,868
than just putting it in randomly.

397
00:19:27,309 --> 00:19:29,511
It waits till you've played a whole bunch of games.

398
00:19:30,719 --> 00:19:32,859
because then we can assume that the player is engaged.

399
00:19:32,980 --> 00:19:35,340
And then, you know, if they get a pretty good score,

400
00:19:35,361 --> 00:19:36,281
or even their best score,

401
00:19:36,301 --> 00:19:38,822
then we think that might be a good time to let them know

402
00:19:38,902 --> 00:19:40,443
that now's a good time to raid us.

403
00:19:40,983 --> 00:19:43,184
If they had it, like, right after a crummy run,

404
00:19:43,204 --> 00:19:44,084
then that's not so good.

405
00:19:44,184 --> 00:19:46,605
Also, if they hit no thanks, we never bug them again.

406
00:19:46,625 --> 00:19:49,627
I don't see any point pestering people into it.

407
00:19:49,647 --> 00:19:51,547
I don't see, like, when they see it for the ninth time

408
00:19:51,567 --> 00:19:53,328
that they're gonna have a change of heart

409
00:19:53,408 --> 00:19:54,809
and give us a five-star rating.

410
00:19:56,970 --> 00:19:58,030
The other thing we wanted to do,

411
00:19:58,090 --> 00:19:59,411
so this was to meet our...

412
00:20:00,372 --> 00:20:03,515
user engagement and community engagement was the dragon fruit.

413
00:20:03,575 --> 00:20:05,536
So the dragon fruit is this really, really rare fruit.

414
00:20:05,916 --> 00:20:09,959
It has a 1 in 40,000 chance of coming up with each fruit spawn,

415
00:20:10,340 --> 00:20:11,340
only in classic mode.

416
00:20:11,821 --> 00:20:13,882
There's some other kind of probability clamping,

417
00:20:13,942 --> 00:20:16,044
and we fudge with the numbers quite a bit to, you know,

418
00:20:16,064 --> 00:20:18,166
make sure it doesn't come up too often or too rarely.

419
00:20:19,807 --> 00:20:21,048
And, yeah, we put that in as well,

420
00:20:21,088 --> 00:20:24,130
just as a nice little thing to try and get people talking.

421
00:20:25,151 --> 00:20:27,032
And the really cool thing was once it came out...

422
00:20:27,676 --> 00:20:29,357
people really were talking about it.

423
00:20:30,417 --> 00:20:32,278
These are some comments that I just copy-pasted

424
00:20:32,298 --> 00:20:33,859
straight off the Touch Arcade forums.

425
00:20:34,379 --> 00:20:36,340
And it kind of started to bring on this mythos,

426
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:38,741
like people weren't even sure it was real or not.

427
00:20:38,941 --> 00:20:40,682
And people would claim that they'd seen it.

428
00:20:40,702 --> 00:20:42,803
It was amazing, the dialogue that we had going.

429
00:20:43,263 --> 00:20:44,383
And this is my favorite one.

430
00:20:45,184 --> 00:20:47,785
People speculating about what the dragon fruit does.

431
00:20:48,605 --> 00:20:51,006
Speculating that maybe it avoids your swipes.

432
00:20:52,107 --> 00:20:56,309
It most certainly does not, but that was just so cool that people were coming up with that.

433
00:20:56,329 --> 00:20:58,551
So it really felt like we met our goal there.

434
00:21:00,612 --> 00:21:02,713
The other thing that happened is, you know, our ratings...

435
00:21:03,455 --> 00:21:06,438
went way up with just adding that little rate it now thing.

436
00:21:06,518 --> 00:21:09,161
No longer were people going to rate us to let us know

437
00:21:09,181 --> 00:21:11,363
that they hated us or that it was broken.

438
00:21:11,723 --> 00:21:12,924
You know, we were getting a lot of one...

439
00:21:13,485 --> 00:21:15,667
We were sitting at about four stars previously,

440
00:21:15,687 --> 00:21:17,449
and a lot of that was, you know,

441
00:21:17,809 --> 00:21:19,871
a lot of five stars and a lot of one stars.

442
00:21:19,891 --> 00:21:21,393
We wouldn't get many in between.

443
00:21:21,453 --> 00:21:23,515
And all the time in the one stars, it was people telling us

444
00:21:23,535 --> 00:21:24,736
about it's broken, which is great.

445
00:21:24,876 --> 00:21:27,358
We need to know when it's broken and under what conditions

446
00:21:27,378 --> 00:21:28,680
and what needs to be fixed about it.

447
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:33,063
But there was no one, not that many people going there to tell us that they liked it.

448
00:21:33,804 --> 00:21:36,386
And it was great, we did this, and all of a sudden people were on our side.

449
00:21:36,446 --> 00:21:39,349
They were there and letting us know that they liked the game.

450
00:21:39,689 --> 00:21:40,950
Sometimes they do things like,

451
00:21:41,511 --> 00:21:43,392
awesome game and give you one star.

452
00:21:44,433 --> 00:21:47,536
Often accompanied by, this game is terrible, five stars.

453
00:21:48,717 --> 00:21:51,259
Sometimes I wonder if like maybe they're confused and it's like golf.

454
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:55,143
So, lower score is better. Hole in one, good job guys, one star.

455
00:21:57,425 --> 00:21:59,106
So yeah, and then this is what happened.

456
00:21:59,226 --> 00:22:03,629
So the orange spike on your left there is the Zenmode update,

457
00:22:03,949 --> 00:22:05,470
and then this is the Chaser update.

458
00:22:05,730 --> 00:22:07,791
So you can see it dropped pretty quickly afterwards.

459
00:22:08,892 --> 00:22:11,633
And our sales went way up.

460
00:22:11,673 --> 00:22:13,954
You can see there it's made a really obvious,

461
00:22:13,974 --> 00:22:15,916
a really dramatic difference on sales,

462
00:22:15,936 --> 00:22:17,396
which was absolutely fantastic.

463
00:22:17,717 --> 00:22:20,178
And I really attribute that mostly towards the ratings,

464
00:22:20,238 --> 00:22:21,459
not so much the dragon fruit.

465
00:22:22,663 --> 00:22:23,844
So that was really excellent.

466
00:22:23,884 --> 00:22:25,804
And we also managed to address all of the bugs.

467
00:22:25,844 --> 00:22:28,865
That really helped stabilize our star rating as well.

468
00:22:28,905 --> 00:22:30,465
And so the people who downloaded it,

469
00:22:31,466 --> 00:22:34,406
who got the Chaser update, who had been having problems,

470
00:22:34,446 --> 00:22:36,147
had all their problems addressed really quickly.

471
00:22:36,207 --> 00:22:36,867
So they were happy.

472
00:22:37,187 --> 00:22:38,947
And then the people who weren't having problems,

473
00:22:39,007 --> 00:22:41,328
everything was working fine, they got some extra new stuff.

474
00:22:41,368 --> 00:22:42,928
They got the dragon fruit and the coconuts.

475
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:44,549
So they were happy as well.

476
00:22:46,229 --> 00:22:47,890
So we were really happy with this.

477
00:22:47,930 --> 00:22:50,110
We really felt like the Chasers was a good model.

478
00:22:50,898 --> 00:22:56,723
It was important to make sure that we had the content side of the chaser ready to go before the previous update even landed

479
00:22:56,783 --> 00:23:02,048
So we could respond to the bugs in a timely fashion. This is a model that we've been using a fair bit

480
00:23:02,068 --> 00:23:07,072
I won't cover any other kind of chaser updates because they follow the same sort of model that we even use it for jetpack

481
00:23:07,092 --> 00:23:12,937
Joyride and monster dash and all of our iOS games now and also we learned that ratings matter

482
00:23:14,298 --> 00:23:16,260
It's probably no great revelation there

483
00:23:18,570 --> 00:23:19,631
So now we move on to update 1.3.

484
00:23:20,691 --> 00:23:23,552
At this point, our player base has grown to about half a million people.

485
00:23:24,432 --> 00:23:26,853
And our goal was really to make the game more sticky.

486
00:23:27,253 --> 00:23:30,854
We really wanted people to spend more time playing Fruit Ninja.

487
00:23:32,035 --> 00:23:34,256
It seemed like, you know, people loved the game.

488
00:23:34,296 --> 00:23:35,496
They told us how much they liked it,

489
00:23:35,516 --> 00:23:37,737
but they would kind of play it for about an hour or two,

490
00:23:37,777 --> 00:23:39,137
and then they would burn out on it.

491
00:23:39,237 --> 00:23:42,838
You know, maybe some friends would get some really competitive stuff going on,

492
00:23:42,878 --> 00:23:44,619
and they'd be really socially driven.

493
00:23:45,099 --> 00:23:48,100
But we certainly weren't getting people spending a huge amount of time

494
00:23:48,140 --> 00:23:48,360
in the...

495
00:23:49,860 --> 00:23:53,282
So to make it sticky, we figured, hey, we need some long-term goals with rewards,

496
00:23:53,342 --> 00:23:56,744
which pretty much sounds like every shop system ever made in every game.

497
00:23:57,705 --> 00:23:58,945
So we started working on that.

498
00:24:01,227 --> 00:24:05,889
We already knew what we wanted people to be able to buy and unlock.

499
00:24:06,270 --> 00:24:10,792
We already had these funky blades from when we worked on the critical waves for Zen mode,

500
00:24:11,053 --> 00:24:15,355
where we could easily color the blades, add particle effects, do kinds of funky stuff with that.

501
00:24:15,395 --> 00:24:16,416
So that was a no-brainer.

502
00:24:16,896 --> 00:24:19,538
And again, adding backgrounds, that's a nice easy one as well.

503
00:24:20,572 --> 00:24:22,614
It was easy pre-retina days at least.

504
00:24:22,674 --> 00:24:26,456
It gets a bit trickier now with how much space it takes up on a retina display.

505
00:24:27,217 --> 00:24:28,738
So we had that sorted quite quickly.

506
00:24:29,498 --> 00:24:34,341
What we weren't sure about was whether people should be allowed to have custom backgrounds.

507
00:24:37,349 --> 00:24:41,791
Just yesterday in my hotel I realized that I didn't have a screenshot for this background.

508
00:24:41,931 --> 00:24:45,132
So I got on Skype and I talked to Woody, one of our programmers back in Brisbane.

509
00:24:45,152 --> 00:24:47,792
I said, hey, can you just hack up a Fruit Ninja build

510
00:24:48,473 --> 00:24:52,974
and, like, hack in some random stupid background and send me a screenshot of it?

511
00:24:53,194 --> 00:24:55,175
This is the first screenshot he sent me.

512
00:24:55,195 --> 00:24:58,416
It's like, is this one alright? I'm like, that is perfect.

513
00:25:00,549 --> 00:25:02,250
And really what we decided was, you know,

514
00:25:02,950 --> 00:25:05,671
we didn't want to allow people to do their own custom backgrounds

515
00:25:05,691 --> 00:25:09,273
because we really felt like it kind of took away from the vibe and the feel of the game

516
00:25:09,313 --> 00:25:13,074
and sort of people were obviously going to do all kinds of crazy stuff.

517
00:25:13,114 --> 00:25:18,017
We had, you know, you can kind of imagine the stuff that's going to end up in Google image search.

518
00:25:18,117 --> 00:25:22,599
And not only that, but we spent a lot of time mucking around with the backgrounds we had

519
00:25:22,679 --> 00:25:26,360
to make sure that they, you could, the fruit was really visible on there.

520
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:27,981
Like there's a lot of contrast with the fruit.

521
00:25:28,261 --> 00:25:30,682
And we often use really dark, plain backgrounds

522
00:25:30,702 --> 00:25:32,703
because it provides a lot of contrast with the juice,

523
00:25:32,763 --> 00:25:34,124
which is a really important part.

524
00:25:34,204 --> 00:25:37,826
So we wanted to maintain some authorial control over that.

525
00:25:40,947 --> 00:25:42,428
So then we started working on the shop.

526
00:25:42,508 --> 00:25:44,189
And the shop was damn tricky.

527
00:25:44,689 --> 00:25:47,210
We'd come up with this really clever novel design

528
00:25:47,230 --> 00:25:49,071
for our menus that everything is sliceable.

529
00:25:50,237 --> 00:25:54,358
and there are no shops that involve slicing a pineapple to buy things.

530
00:25:54,758 --> 00:25:57,499
The thing is, people had come in and they'd bought Fruit Ninja

531
00:25:57,539 --> 00:25:59,239
and they'd done it in the iTunes Store,

532
00:25:59,359 --> 00:26:02,760
and that uses such a different interface convention to what we were using.

533
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:06,841
This was just so crazy, kind of off track,

534
00:26:06,981 --> 00:26:09,742
and it was really a massive, massive challenge for us to do,

535
00:26:09,822 --> 00:26:13,303
something that would intuitively rely mostly on swiping and slicing.

536
00:26:13,643 --> 00:26:15,363
We really didn't want it to go into, you know,

537
00:26:15,403 --> 00:26:18,164
some kind of finicky, picky, touch-based thing.

538
00:26:18,184 --> 00:26:19,824
We wanted to keep it very Fruit Ninja.

539
00:26:21,225 --> 00:26:25,886
So this is what we came up with. I couldn't find any work in progress from those, unfortunately.

540
00:26:26,506 --> 00:26:29,527
Although, rest assured, there were plenty of terrible, horrible designs.

541
00:26:30,668 --> 00:26:33,069
Maybe it's good I'm not showing you. It might be a little bit embarrassing.

542
00:26:33,109 --> 00:26:35,450
But this is what we came up with in the end.

543
00:26:35,990 --> 00:26:38,070
You know, we made a couple of little concessions as well.

544
00:26:38,090 --> 00:26:42,652
We were like, okay, there might be people that are still kind of expecting it to work, like...

545
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:48,141
the app store. So we actually made our icons for the things that you could unlock, glossy

546
00:26:48,221 --> 00:26:52,202
and rounded corners, and if you tap on them, then it would automatically scroll up to there

547
00:26:52,243 --> 00:26:59,505
as well. So then, one of the really big problems we had then was, you know, we had it in there,

548
00:26:59,545 --> 00:27:05,167
it was selectable, that was fine. Originally we had it that instead of the current system

549
00:27:05,187 --> 00:27:09,308
where it is now, where you unlock it by completing tasks, it originally worked.

550
00:27:09,835 --> 00:27:12,898
like a shop, you know, by playing you would kind of earn currency

551
00:27:13,258 --> 00:27:16,541
and then you would spend that currency, you know, unlocking things.

552
00:27:17,702 --> 00:27:20,965
And again it was this weird thing where, you know, we're playing it, the whole team's

553
00:27:20,985 --> 00:27:23,507
playing it and they're like, yeah, it works, but

554
00:27:23,907 --> 00:27:27,751
for some reason it just doesn't feel Fruit Ninja. We kind of had this same

555
00:27:27,831 --> 00:27:28,671
problem again where

556
00:27:28,952 --> 00:27:31,574
something that we expected to work and that seemed fine

557
00:27:31,954 --> 00:27:34,677
really wasn't working for our game. It just didn't feel

558
00:27:35,057 --> 00:27:37,239
quite right in there, it didn't feel like it belonged.

559
00:27:38,799 --> 00:27:44,463
So after a lot of mucking around, we ended up coming up with this system where, you know, basically like achievements.

560
00:27:45,504 --> 00:27:50,307
We spent a long time tuning it so that you would unlock them kind of in a fairly progressive manner.

561
00:27:50,728 --> 00:27:55,451
Early on you would do it and if you were a really good player, you would unlock like five blades in the first game

562
00:27:55,471 --> 00:27:57,453
and then you'd have this big drought where nothing happens.

563
00:27:57,473 --> 00:27:59,034
So we spent quite a lot of time tuning that.

564
00:28:01,635 --> 00:28:04,416
And then on release, we had a really solid reception again.

565
00:28:04,436 --> 00:28:05,376
We were really happy with.

566
00:28:05,837 --> 00:28:07,838
The iTunes reviews instantly changed

567
00:28:07,898 --> 00:28:12,580
from asking us to add multi-slice and new modes

568
00:28:12,620 --> 00:28:14,741
and things like that to just, I want this blade,

569
00:28:14,821 --> 00:28:17,062
I want this background, I want custom backgrounds.

570
00:28:17,142 --> 00:28:18,903
It really dramatically changed the way

571
00:28:18,963 --> 00:28:20,284
people were thinking about the game

572
00:28:20,304 --> 00:28:21,324
and what they wanted out of it.

573
00:28:22,124 --> 00:28:24,105
And we didn't have any analytics at this point,

574
00:28:24,165 --> 00:28:26,086
but we just know anecdotally that people

575
00:28:26,106 --> 00:28:27,787
were sticking with the game for longer.

576
00:28:28,107 --> 00:28:28,968
So we were really happy.

577
00:28:29,008 --> 00:28:30,628
We felt like we'd achieved our goal with that.

578
00:28:31,342 --> 00:28:34,946
We also got our ratings crept up a little bit higher again,

579
00:28:35,026 --> 00:28:35,606
which was great.

580
00:28:37,328 --> 00:28:39,190
And this is what the release looked like.

581
00:28:39,230 --> 00:28:41,773
So again, it's kind of similar to this Zenmode one

582
00:28:41,813 --> 00:28:44,395
where it has a bit of a bump, and you

583
00:28:44,415 --> 00:28:46,277
can see the sales kind of get pushed up there.

584
00:28:46,297 --> 00:28:49,140
But really, it hasn't done much at all.

585
00:28:49,901 --> 00:28:51,082
And again, this is a lot of work.

586
00:28:51,102 --> 00:28:51,923
It kind of bummed.

587
00:28:51,963 --> 00:28:54,005
We were hoping, again, for it to explode up there.

588
00:28:55,078 --> 00:28:58,099
The good thing is, is we weren't in that downward decline like we were.

589
00:28:58,459 --> 00:29:00,380
The updates were coming pretty thick and fast,

590
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:02,401
and we kept on adding a lot of value to the game,

591
00:29:02,441 --> 00:29:05,042
and as a result, it was holding quite steady.

592
00:29:05,183 --> 00:29:08,524
So, yeah, we were happy about that, but, you know, we had been hoping for more.

593
00:29:10,865 --> 00:29:12,786
So, the lessons we learned was, you know,

594
00:29:12,806 --> 00:29:16,028
while we were achieving our goals of, you know, making the game sticky,

595
00:29:16,068 --> 00:29:18,209
it was really important for us to not compromise

596
00:29:18,249 --> 00:29:20,390
what had made the game successful in the first place.

597
00:29:21,154 --> 00:29:24,737
you know, we could go through and hack things up and change it around, but, you know, if

598
00:29:25,377 --> 00:29:29,180
Fruit Ninja doesn't remain what Fruit Ninja is about, then that's going to be a huge disaster,

599
00:29:29,220 --> 00:29:33,664
a huge mistake. And also, again, you know, updates are not a magical silver bullet.

600
00:29:35,405 --> 00:29:36,586
So, update 1.4.

601
00:29:38,342 --> 00:29:40,904
Our current player base is now at about one million players.

602
00:29:41,664 --> 00:29:42,885
It's time to make another mode.

603
00:29:42,945 --> 00:29:44,526
That worked out pretty good last time.

604
00:29:44,606 --> 00:29:47,288
Zen mode got a lot of media coverage, so that was cool.

605
00:29:47,388 --> 00:29:49,729
And we figured this time we could do another mode,

606
00:29:49,749 --> 00:29:52,431
but this time it would be bigger and better and more badass

607
00:29:52,471 --> 00:29:53,171
than Zen mode.

608
00:29:55,873 --> 00:29:58,835
So what everyone was saying, and I mean it was pretty obvious,

609
00:29:58,875 --> 00:30:01,556
like a lot of people were saying it in the office as well,

610
00:30:01,636 --> 00:30:03,097
was power-ups, right?

611
00:30:03,137 --> 00:30:05,459
Like, hey, let's have a mode with power-ups in it.

612
00:30:05,619 --> 00:30:08,060
We'll make them bananas, because it's a mystery banana mode.

613
00:30:08,596 --> 00:30:10,377
That seemed cool, so we started working on that.

614
00:30:10,858 --> 00:30:14,500
At the time, we were kind of influenced a bit by Bejeweled Blitz,

615
00:30:14,821 --> 00:30:17,423
which is ironic, because I think they were right before me in this room.

616
00:30:18,183 --> 00:30:22,286
And we took a bit of inspiration from there, we had a 60 second time limit,

617
00:30:22,326 --> 00:30:24,588
and we started adding power-ups galore.

618
00:30:25,029 --> 00:30:29,792
So you can see there a screenshot of an early build that had the frenzy banana in it.

619
00:30:30,345 --> 00:30:35,206
and we had the freeze banana and the score multiplier banana which is all stuff that is still in the game

620
00:30:35,226 --> 00:30:41,027
but we had all kinds of crazy shit in there. We had this gravity well banana where you would slice it and it would make this black hole

621
00:30:41,367 --> 00:30:47,628
and then the fruit would come up and kind of get sucked into the black hole and all just sit there so you can swipe it all at once and get like a hundred fruit combo.

622
00:30:48,789 --> 00:30:58,871
We had crazy waterfalls of fruit and time traveling bananas that would rewind the game but not your score and all kinds of wacky crazy stuff.

623
00:31:00,051 --> 00:31:02,352
but somehow it felt like it needed more.

624
00:31:03,632 --> 00:31:07,373
So again, kind of, you know, at this point we were drawing things from

625
00:31:08,193 --> 00:31:11,294
Bejeweled Blitz and taking a lot of inspiration from that, because I was just like

626
00:31:11,394 --> 00:31:14,756
hopelessly addicted any time I wasn't working on Fruit Ninja, I was playing that.

627
00:31:15,216 --> 00:31:17,977
We came up with this idea of Starfruit, when you slice Starfruit,

628
00:31:18,397 --> 00:31:21,758
coins would come out, and then at the end of the game, if you had enough coins, you

629
00:31:21,778 --> 00:31:22,858
could buy these power-ups.

630
00:31:23,498 --> 00:31:25,759
So, you know, like turning off bombs and things like that.

631
00:31:26,439 --> 00:31:28,140
So we were working away on that for a while.

632
00:31:29,194 --> 00:31:32,055
And at this point we're at about six weeks worth of work,

633
00:31:32,075 --> 00:31:36,176
so again, about how long it took to make the first version of Fruit Ninja,

634
00:31:36,216 --> 00:31:37,016
which is kind of nuts.

635
00:31:37,696 --> 00:31:40,617
And things are looking good, but it's just not quite popping yet.

636
00:31:40,697 --> 00:31:41,937
It still needs some love.

637
00:31:42,297 --> 00:31:44,318
So, you know, we're still working along on it.

638
00:31:45,878 --> 00:31:48,459
And then, this happened.

639
00:31:49,879 --> 00:31:52,700
We'll get to the office one day, and surprise!

640
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:53,820
Game Center is a thing.

641
00:31:55,134 --> 00:32:00,218
and it has all these crazy cool features like inviting friends and matchmaking and you know

642
00:32:00,558 --> 00:32:03,580
real-time multiplayer and leaderboards and achievements.

643
00:32:05,401 --> 00:32:09,804
So, we changed our mind on what we were doing.

644
00:32:11,030 --> 00:32:14,093
And even though we had this kind of half-complete mode that was getting there,

645
00:32:14,113 --> 00:32:14,974
it was starting to feel good.

646
00:32:14,994 --> 00:32:16,976
We were like, right, screw that.

647
00:32:17,336 --> 00:32:18,537
Let's put that on the back burner.

648
00:32:19,098 --> 00:32:22,921
Let's be one of the first real-time multiplayer games out using Game Center.

649
00:32:23,202 --> 00:32:25,244
Let's do that. Let's strike while the iron is hot.

650
00:32:25,264 --> 00:32:26,225
Let's be those guys.

651
00:32:28,648 --> 00:32:32,209
So here's a screenshot. I don't have any work in progress shots of this because

652
00:32:32,490 --> 00:32:36,811
somehow, someway, this mode was designed in four days flat.

653
00:32:37,352 --> 00:32:40,513
This is right off the back of spending six weeks on a mode and only getting

654
00:32:40,573 --> 00:32:43,414
halfway there. Multiplayer was knocked out in about four days

655
00:32:43,915 --> 00:32:47,356
and implemented in just over that as well because we were kind of implementing and

656
00:32:47,376 --> 00:32:48,757
designing at the same time to

657
00:32:49,097 --> 00:32:51,338
to really get it to market extremely quickly.

658
00:32:52,576 --> 00:32:59,339
It was kind of cool because the multiplayer was so novel, it was kind of almost easier to design for.

659
00:32:59,359 --> 00:33:05,062
It kept everyone's fruit on the same screen, just to kind of create that sense of connectedness,

660
00:33:05,482 --> 00:33:09,884
like you're really interacting with someone else and you're kind of sharing that spatial location.

661
00:33:10,464 --> 00:33:14,165
We did a lot of tricks to kind of hide how much lag there was in the system,

662
00:33:14,185 --> 00:33:15,126
because it was pretty early.

663
00:33:15,166 --> 00:33:20,487
And, you know, yeah, the coverage we got for that was just mental.

664
00:33:20,947 --> 00:33:23,368
We got a huge amount of press for being one of the first.

665
00:33:23,668 --> 00:33:26,609
We had really positive reviews on the mode, which was encouraging,

666
00:33:26,629 --> 00:33:27,970
because we hadn't spent that long on it.

667
00:33:27,990 --> 00:33:31,251
But, you know, definitely that kind of novelty factor of playing against people

668
00:33:31,271 --> 00:33:34,652
and being, I'm better than you at Fruit Ninja, really, really worked.

669
00:33:35,452 --> 00:33:38,933
And most importantly, we got a lot of love from Apple for doing this.

670
00:33:39,819 --> 00:33:44,041
because you know as soon as they release something new they really want to promote and tell everyone

671
00:33:44,081 --> 00:33:48,082
about how good it was and we were there right at the front right at the beginning when it first

672
00:33:48,142 --> 00:33:53,004
launched so you know we got re-featured they did a game center category and we were right near the

673
00:33:53,044 --> 00:33:58,066
top of that and a multiplayer category and we were in that and you know we got so much attention for

674
00:33:58,086 --> 00:33:59,027
it which was fantastic.

675
00:34:00,347 --> 00:34:05,030
So this one here, the very first spike on the left, that is multiplayer.

676
00:34:05,150 --> 00:34:08,052
And the second one is when we brought in achievements and leaderboards.

677
00:34:08,092 --> 00:34:10,875
We actually left that off the first implementation of Game Center,

678
00:34:11,255 --> 00:34:14,677
just so we could hit market fast and, you know, almost first.

679
00:34:15,543 --> 00:34:18,487
And then, you know, we also put in a couple of tweaks to multiplayer in there.

680
00:34:18,608 --> 00:34:20,511
Again, not unlike the kind of Chaser model.

681
00:34:20,931 --> 00:34:24,417
And you can see this had a profound long-term impact on the game.

682
00:34:24,797 --> 00:34:27,442
It really did lift it up and the amount of exposure

683
00:34:27,462 --> 00:34:30,446
just really helped Fruit Ninja immensely.

684
00:34:32,423 --> 00:34:33,963
So we learned a few lessons at this point.

685
00:34:34,624 --> 00:34:35,964
You can't plan everything.

686
00:34:36,324 --> 00:34:39,106
This is obviously not part of the game plan, game center

687
00:34:39,126 --> 00:34:39,566
coming out.

688
00:34:39,606 --> 00:34:41,987
The mobile market is crazy, and sometimes we

689
00:34:42,027 --> 00:34:43,887
feel like we've got to be crazy to keep up with it.

690
00:34:45,128 --> 00:34:46,729
Even though we kind of dropped what we were doing,

691
00:34:46,769 --> 00:34:49,290
and we did this mad dash, and it was all this kind of insane

692
00:34:49,310 --> 00:34:51,811
scenario, we definitely feel like we made the right decision

693
00:34:51,991 --> 00:34:52,511
in doing that.

694
00:34:53,611 --> 00:34:55,753
And you know that top-level visibility matters when

695
00:34:56,133 --> 00:34:59,715
when you're there and you're getting massive amounts of coverage across the

696
00:34:59,755 --> 00:35:01,395
sites. That made a huge difference.

697
00:35:02,056 --> 00:35:06,278
There's absolutely no doubt about it. So where were we?

698
00:35:07,238 --> 00:35:10,800
Oh yeah, Arcade Mode. So Arcade Mode is now 1.5.

699
00:35:12,401 --> 00:35:15,003
We now, you know, we spent quite a bit of time on the

700
00:35:15,583 --> 00:35:19,025
supporting the multiplayer update. We're at about 2.1 million player base.

701
00:35:19,703 --> 00:35:23,347
We really want to finish off arcade mode and we want to completely blow everyone away.

702
00:35:23,627 --> 00:35:25,028
We're starting to feel the pressure, right?

703
00:35:25,068 --> 00:35:27,630
Like, this mode, we've been teasing for a long time.

704
00:35:28,571 --> 00:35:30,713
And people are starting to get a bit sketchy about, you know,

705
00:35:30,733 --> 00:35:32,755
whether when we promise there's going to be another mode,

706
00:35:33,115 --> 00:35:35,317
this banana mode, whether it was a real thing or not.

707
00:35:37,448 --> 00:35:39,949
So at this point the mode kind of looks like this.

708
00:35:40,630 --> 00:35:42,470
There's some interesting things you'll notice about this

709
00:35:42,510 --> 00:35:44,791
that are different from the actual version of arcade mode

710
00:35:44,811 --> 00:35:45,291
that's in there.

