00:37:38,888 --> 00:37:39,749
Got rid of all of that.

749
00:37:40,830 --> 00:37:43,471
It was just kind of making our results screen too clunky,

750
00:37:43,531 --> 00:37:44,272
too complicated.

751
00:37:44,292 --> 00:37:46,393
Whenever a casual player would get to that screen,

752
00:37:46,733 --> 00:37:49,215
you'd just see their eyes kind of glaze over.

753
00:37:49,355 --> 00:37:52,537
And there's a lot of buttons and a lot of interactions

754
00:37:52,577 --> 00:37:53,218
going on there.

755
00:37:53,938 --> 00:37:56,320
The other thing we did is we started kind of stripping back

756
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:58,581
the amount of information that we were presenting the player

757
00:37:59,001 --> 00:38:00,422
to make it a bit more vague.

758
00:38:02,764 --> 00:38:06,748
So, like, one of the big things we did was, you know, the frenzy bar at the top, we actually

759
00:38:06,828 --> 00:38:09,851
removed that bar and we just let it play out for about seven seconds.

760
00:38:10,832 --> 00:38:12,794
And we weren't telling people how far they were through it.

761
00:38:13,054 --> 00:38:17,519
We started relying on people to just kind of intuitively get a sense for how long these

762
00:38:17,559 --> 00:38:18,300
things were going to last.

763
00:38:18,320 --> 00:38:20,522
We did the same with the combo blitz as well.

764
00:38:22,784 --> 00:38:24,326
And once we cut things...

765
00:38:25,345 --> 00:38:27,786
there was all of a sudden it felt like this kind of new life and this,

766
00:38:28,026 --> 00:38:30,626
these new opportunities before things have been complicated

767
00:38:31,266 --> 00:38:34,607
and we kind of been missing these, these interactions we could do.

768
00:38:34,707 --> 00:38:39,448
As soon as we cut these bars, we could stick like freeze and frenzy bananas together

769
00:38:39,508 --> 00:38:40,748
and that was awesome.

770
00:38:41,208 --> 00:38:45,349
All the fruit pouring in from the side and it's in slow-mo and it was totally badass

771
00:38:45,409 --> 00:38:47,630
and just by stripping things back and simplifying,

772
00:38:47,890 --> 00:38:49,530
we'd allowed all these new opportunities.

773
00:38:51,630 --> 00:38:54,811
The other big thing we did was, you know, we made the blitzing visibility.

774
00:38:56,165 --> 00:39:02,268
really different. Before we had bars counting up, and again we were trying to do so much to explain to the player exactly how it worked.

775
00:39:02,729 --> 00:39:06,911
And instead we came with this new philosophy of, let's kind of hide it from the players a bit.

776
00:39:07,351 --> 00:39:10,492
Casual players might not ever get a combo blitz, and that's fine.

777
00:39:10,952 --> 00:39:16,275
We don't need to have like this kind of empty bar on the side that's just sort of taunting them, telling them they're not doing very good.

778
00:39:16,475 --> 00:39:18,136
If they don't ever know about it, then that's fine.

779
00:39:18,812 --> 00:39:24,136
So we kind of, rather than having bars, we have these lines in the background that are kind of quite faint,

780
00:39:24,176 --> 00:39:27,479
and they fade away and slow down, and that's how you know how much you have left.

781
00:39:28,580 --> 00:39:33,164
We bring the score right up in your face because we wanted people to know the reward they were getting,

782
00:39:33,204 --> 00:39:35,185
but not necessarily how it worked or why.

783
00:39:35,466 --> 00:39:38,428
And the great thing is, is casual players now, they're just playing along, that's fine.

784
00:39:38,528 --> 00:39:42,952
As they get better, as they start stringing combos together, they start to see this stuff pop up.

785
00:39:43,443 --> 00:39:45,464
They're like, hmm, okay, I really want to get a better score.

786
00:39:45,484 --> 00:39:46,665
I'm going to learn this system.

787
00:39:47,706 --> 00:39:50,247
And, you know, they spend a little bit of time figuring it out,

788
00:39:50,287 --> 00:39:52,409
and, you know, for an advanced player, it's fine.

789
00:39:52,429 --> 00:39:53,389
They've got it understood.

790
00:39:53,829 --> 00:39:55,691
And so by changing the visibility

791
00:39:55,731 --> 00:39:58,332
and how much information we were presenting the player with,

792
00:39:58,452 --> 00:40:00,113
it really, really improved the design.

793
00:40:01,857 --> 00:40:03,638
And then we couldn't imagine the game without it.

794
00:40:03,718 --> 00:40:07,381
At some point, we were just spending all of our time playing arcade mode.

795
00:40:07,401 --> 00:40:10,964
We were taking screenshots and, like, sending it to the QA guys

