00:40:15,988 --> 00:40:18,110
because we spent six hours a day competing.

799
00:40:18,870 --> 00:40:22,333
And it's kind of, that's when it struck us that that's how we knew that it was ready.

800
00:40:22,974 --> 00:40:26,236
And now, whenever we add another major update to the game...

801
00:40:27,135 --> 00:40:29,316
That's kind of our measure for whether it's ready or not.

802
00:40:29,436 --> 00:40:32,277
Once it's at the point where we can't imagine it without it,

803
00:40:32,297 --> 00:40:35,398
where we go home and I use my phone that has the store-bought

804
00:40:35,438 --> 00:40:37,459
version on it, and I go straight for that mode,

805
00:40:37,479 --> 00:40:40,520
I'm like, ugh, damn, it's missing feature 1, 2, and 3

806
00:40:40,800 --> 00:40:41,521
in the new version.

807
00:40:42,161 --> 00:40:45,102
That's our metric for, OK, this thing's ready to go.

808
00:40:45,202 --> 00:40:47,023
Let's get this out there and get this out to people.

809
00:40:49,343 --> 00:40:50,804
Yeah, if we finally released it.

